newsitem.title: USA: Healthcare COMPARE sees 96 EPS around $2.25.
newsitem.headline: Healthcare COMPARE sees 96 EPS around $2.25.

text.p: Healthcare COMPARE Corp Chief Financial Officer Joseph Whitters said on Wednesday the company expects its 1996 earnings per share at around $2.25.
"As we finish this year our earnings will be around $2.25," a share, Whitters told a Piper Jaffray healthcare services conference.
Healthcare COMPARE earned $1.89 a share in 1995. Wall Street's consensus estimate for the company's 1996 earnings is for $2.24 a share, according to First Call.
A graphic presented by Whitters at the conference showed the company's estimated 1996 revenues at around $250 million, up from a reported $214 million in 1995.
